array.note: s[i] is the node that succeeds to the ith node in the tour (value i if unused)
p[i] is the position (starting at 0) of the ith node in the tour (-1 if unused)
g[i] is the gain collected when going from the ith node to its successor in the tour

intension.note: node 0 is the first node of the tour

group.note: each node appears at most once during the tour

block.note: linking variables from s and p

maximize.note: maximizing the sum of collected gains
